snippet: Armed with guns and rocket-propelled grenades, rival Libyan militias fought on the streets of Tripoli, Libyan officials said, highlighting the country’s persisting lawlessness and insecurity.
abstract: At least five people are wounded as rival Libyan militias clash with heavy weapons in Tripoli, highlighting the dangers posed by thousands of armed men who refuse to yield to the new government’s control; car bomb explodes outside a police station in Benghazi, wounding at least three police officers and further indicating the country's instability.
lead_paragraph: Armed with guns and rocket-propelled grenades, rival Libyan militias fought on the streets of Tripoli, Libyan officials said, highlighting the country’s persisting lawlessness and insecurity.

headline.seo: Clashes and Car Bombing Highlight Insecurity in Libya
headline.main: Clashes and Car Bombing Highlight Insecurity Across Libya
